inn1.comm: starts off with a no ball, bowled short on middle and leg, worked away off the back foot to fine leg
Tendulkar goes for it, its fired in full on middle, he makes room and drags it wide of midwicket, didn't time it well enough but gets a couple of runs
oversteps again, false start by Mills, short of a length outside off and got some away movement there, left alone, bit time for another free hit

gets it right this time, juicy, overpitched ball outside off stump, makes room and steers it beautifully through the point region for a boundary, he's actually overstepped again but the umpire didn't spot it
back to normal now, short of a good length on the off stump, pushed off the back foot towards cover
better, good length on the off stump, Tendulkar gets forward and defends it solidly back to Mills
a touch too short, on middle and leg, worked away off his hips to fine leg
short and wide but Sehwag is not onto it well enough, mistimes an attempted cut towards short cover
good length on middle, pushed off the front foot to mid-on
fuller on the off stump and moving away, defended with a lunge towards cover
shortish outside off, tries to open the face and play it square, mistimes it to cover
bowled on a good length outside off, stayed low but Tendulkar lets it go
given a wide though it wasn;t quite one, landed full outside off and moved away, Tendulkar left it alone
kept low again, Tendulkar had shaped himself for a drive through mid-off on the back foot, ended up getting an inside edge behind square
bowled full on middle and leg, tries to drive it past midwicket, probably got a thin edge onto the pads and it seemed as though it was going down anyway

appeal for run out, he's in comfortably, pushed away to square leg and Grant Elliot throws down the stumps at the striker's end with an under-am flick as they try to steal a single but he's managed to get his bat in the crease, though he didn't slide it as he should, it was in the air for quite some time
short on middle, tries to pull it away over midwicket, misses, is struck on the thighs
good length on middle, driven back past Mills off the back foot for a couple, well timed

timber! Bowled straight on middle, similar to the previous delivery, Sehwag goes for a cross-batted heave over midwicket, it seemed as if the ball kept just a little low, he missed and the stumps took a beating. New Zealand have struck early, removing India's most explosive batsman
bang on target, bowled on a good length on middle, held its line, defended watchfully back to the bowler
good length outside off and going away with the angle, left alone
straying down leg side, given a wide
length ball on middle and off, a hint of away movement, driven with a full face to mid-on
held it back just a touch, bowled outside off, Tendulkar pushes it firmly to mid-off
short of a length outside off and Tendulkar cashes in, gets back and cuts it away fiercely between point and cover
back of a length outside off, thinks of playing the cut again but it's a little too wide so he withdraws at the last moment
fuller outside off, leaves it be
short of a good length on the off stump, dropped into the leg side off the back foot and they scamper a single

superbly timed, slightly short on middle, gets back and flicks it away through square leg, raced off the bat and beat a diving Butler to the boundary. He dived full stretch to drag that back in, but made contact with the ropes
bowled on a good length on middle and leg, turns it away to fine leg
back of a length on the off stump, just dabbed in front of midwicket and they set off for a single
well played, a low full toss on middle, closes the face to push it between midwicket and mid-on for a couple
mistimed, short of a good length outside off, tries to cut it away through point but ends up playing it straight to cover
beaten! Angling into the batsman from wide of the crease and moves away after pitching just as Tendulkar came forward to defend
short outside off, cut away past point towards third man
full on the off stump, driven through the line to mid-off
swung in, landed full on middle, Tendulkar tries to drive it past midwicket, gets a thin inside edge onto his pads, stifled appeal but the umpire shakes his head
poor ball, meaty length ball on the pads and Tendulkar just flicks it away in front of square, came off the middle as hot-spot indicates
full outside off, tries to push it into the off side, ends up getting a thick inside edge wide of midwicket
Gambhir into the act now, fraction full outside off, he gets front and across and turns it away wristily wide of square leg
good length on middle, bowled at 132.5 kmph, defended on the leg side
short of a good length outside off, punched off the back foot to cover
straying on the pads, full on leg, glanced down to Ian Butler at fine leg for a single
Gambhir gives the charge and tries to cart that over the infield on the off side, it's a little too wide, fails to reach it
short on middle, paddles it down to fine leg
too straight, works it away wide of Butler at fine leg for a couple
bowled on a good length on middle, pushed to midwicket
full on middle and leg, turned away behind square, fine leg takes some time to gather the ball and they run an easy two
edged, spat off the pitch after landing on a good length on the off stump, Gambhir tries to defend it on the leg side, gets a leading edge that lands short of point
back of a length on leg stump, pushed wide of midwicket for a single
back of a length on middle, defended off the back foot towards short midwicket
fullish outside off, goes for a blazing drive through the off side, the ball flies off the outside edge towards third man
short of a good length on middle, worked away behind square for a single
oversteps, short on leg stump, Gambhir tries to do a repeat of what his partner did the previous ball, is struck on the thighs
escapes, bowled full on the off stump, makes room and creams it straight to cover, who's right on the circle, Gambhir misses out
bowled short of a length outside off, chops it down to third man off the back foot
that's a slog, slower ball bowled full outside off, he picked it, got down on one knee and dismissed it for a one bounce four towards deep midwicket
short of a length on the off stump, cramped for room, defends it on the off side
good length on the off stump, driven straight to mid-off
short outside off, tries to cut, misses
full outside off, driven towards McCullum at mid-off for a quick single, he fumbles
good length on middle and leg, driven off the front foot to mid-on
flicked away through midwicket but there's cover in the deep, bowled a little too straight there, full on middle stump and that's bread and butter for Tendulkar
down the leg side, an extra ball there, Tendulkar tries to glance it down fine but misses
bowled at 136 kmph, full on middle and off, defended solidly to mid-on
back of a length on middle, makes room and chops it to cover, mistimed it there
excellent fielding, guided wide of point where Jesse Ryder dives to his right and quickly throws the ball back in to prevent a single
beats him this time, marginally short outside off, dabs it down to third man
good length on the off stump, opens the face and pushes it away to point
angling down leg, clips off his pads to fine leg
back of a length on the off stump, dropped onto the pitch and calls for a single, Tendulkar wisely sends him back
short of a length outside off, cut away behind point towards third man
short outside off, guided to point
good length on the off stump, defended off the front foot to the bowler
Gambhir had already made up his mind to go after that but didn't pick the slower one, tried to swat that over cover but was too early into the shot, missed it
well played, worked away behind square, it's a little wide of fine leg and they have ample time to come back for the second
bowled straight on middle, kept a little low, Gambhir did well to bring his bat down in time, played it back to the bowler
back of a length on middle, dropped into the leg side, calls for a single but is sent back
bowled short outside leg stump, Tendulkar swivels and tries to dismiss that to the fine-leg boundary, misses but is given a wide
dances down the track, overpitched outside off stump and drives it powerfully but straight to mid-off, he was livid about missing out there

appeal for lbw, bowled short of a length on middle and leg, Tendulkar tries to paddle it fine, is struck on the pads, Butler appeals but the umpire is not convinced. Replays indicate he may have been struck in line with leg, marginal call that
gone! Slightly short outside off, gets some good bounce, Gambhir tries to guide that to third man, gets a thick edge and McGlashan snaps it easily
what a start! Full outside off, there to hit and does so quite beautifully, leans into the drive to bisect the gap between mid-off and cover, a textbook shot that, confidently played
short of a good length on middle, defended to the bowler on the back foot
good length on the off stump, driven off the front foot to cover
fuller, is into the drive again but fails to beat the fielder once more, firmly struck though
slightly overpitched on the off stump, Tendulkar hits that through the line to mid-off
short of a length outside off, kept a little low, Tendulkar bends to guide that to third man, gets an inside edge straight onto McGlashan's pads
superb over so far, angling into Tendulkar from wide of the crease, steered to point, fails to find the gap again
excellent stuff, short of a length on middle, turned away to midwicket, Oram completes a maiden, that too in a powerplay
back of a length on the off stump, Yuvraj stands tall and pushes it wide of the bowler for a single
bowled at 134 kmph, slightly short on middle and off, defended to midwicket

landed on a good length on middle, turned away off the front foot through midwicket, the fielder in the deep has to run a few yards to his left to get to that and the batsmen come back for the second amid all his hard work
a pressure relieving boundary that, bowled full outside off, gets forward and smashes it through the covers, powerfully struck
back of a length on middle, turned away wristily behind square for a single
good length on the off stump, defended with a lunge towards cover
stump-to-stump, good length on middle, worked away behind square for a single
good length outside off, held its line, left alone to the keeper
delicately played, short of a good length outside off, late-cuts it to third man, gets only a single for his efforts
full on middle, driven with a full face to long-on
good length on the off stump, defended solidly on the off side
bowled at 115 kmph, targeting middle and off, opens the face to dab it to point
reaches his 92nd ODI half-century with a glance down to the fine-leg boundary, bowled quick on the leg stump and he helps it on its way, a steady innings by the master
full on the pads, turned away again but this time straight to the fielder in the deep
good length on the off stump, defended cautiously to cover off the front foot
back of a length on middle, gets back and pushes it back to Butler
cut away, fraction short and he seizes the length quickly, gets back and bisects the narrow gap between point and backward point
good length outside off, leans forward and crunches it to cover
he's stepping up here, short outside off, makes room and cuts it away well but straight to deep point
marginally short outside off, chops it down to point off the back foot
held it back again, bowled outside off, defended with an open face to point
short of a good length on the off stump, pushed off the back foot to mid-off
short and wide, gets on the back foot to cut, misses
short and wide, bowled at a quicker-than-normal speed of 127 kmph, Yuvraj lets it go this time
back of a length on the off stump, turns it away between midwicket and square leg for a single
just fractionally short outside off, Yuvraj stands tall and pulls it away over midwicket, that's his trademark shot, fiercely struck but he was still disappointed he didn't clear the ropes
short of a good length on the off stump, punched off the back foot to cover

massive, gets what he wants this time, landed on a good length outside off, he picked the length early and dismisses it over the deep-midwicket boundary, ended up a few rows back in the stands, the first six of the game, also brings the Indian 100
full outside off stump, pushed firmly off the front foot to mid-off
on target, good length on middle, defended back to the bowler
full, bowled down the leg side, McGlashan fumbles and the Indians get some handy extras
short of a good length on the off stump, bowled at 126 kmph, waits for it and then dabs it to third man
too close to cut, just slightly outside off and he tries to chop it wide of point, zips from under his bat to the keeper
got some good bounce this tie, leapt up from a good length outside off, guided to point off the back foot
short and wide, cut away to point, did so quite gently, wasn't looking for a boundary there
well bowled, good length on the off stump bringing him forward, he defends it straight to mid-off
short of a length outside off, chopped down to point, fails to find the gap, end of another steady over from Oram
short on middle and spinning down, turned away off the back foot behind square
slightly short outside off, gets back and slaps it to deep cover
flighted on middle and off, closes the face to push it in the vacant square-leg region for a single
bowled flat on the off stump, defended back to the bowler
tossed up on middle and leg, swept away powerfully behind square, a valiant dive from deep square leg but the ball was hit too well
flighted on middle and leg, flicked away through square leg for a single
just a fraction full outside off, gets forward and plays a flamboyant drive past the bowler and a diving mid-off, also brings the 50 stand
bowled it too short, enough time for Yuvraj to rock back and pull it over midwicket, the Indians are getting a move-on now
good length on middle and off, defended off the front foot with bat close to pad
sightly short on middle, Yuvraj presents the full face to push it back to the bowler
erring in length again but gets away with it, short on the off stump, punched to cover
slower ball bowled at 112 kmph on middle and leg, tries to turn it away on the leg side, is too early into the short, gets a leading edge towards point
full outside off, Tendulkar flicks it away by walking front and across, towards deep square leg

astounding fielding, low full toss on the off stump and that went like a rocket to Broom who threw himself to his left at mid-off to prevent a certain four, Tendulkar was halfway down the pitch and Broom threw it back in, though a little too slowly, and the master dived full length at the non-striker's end to make it back. You don;t often see him diving while he's batting
fullish outside off, pushed wide of Broom this time for a comfortable single
overpitched outside off stump, makes room and slices it towards deep point
just a punch and that's landed 10 rows back over the long-on boundary, full toss outside off and it's just a firm push, how did he manage that? There was no follow through there, the ball's lost now
expensive over, full and wide, Yuvraj makes room and steers it uppishly wide of point, he's looking lethal here
bowled full on middle, makes room and drills it to mid-on

shot of the day! The third man is up and there's a narrow gap between him and point, bowled full on the off stump, Tendulkar waits for it and opens the face to beat those two fielders, delicately done
low full toss on the off stump, steered wide of point for a single
that's disappeared, what a way to bring up his half-century, meaty length ball on middle and off, he stays his ground, gets under it and strikes it cleanly over the long-on boundary
overpitched again, slapped down towards long-off
tries to paddle it fine, gets an inside edge onto his pads and it lobs up on the leg side, they take a quick single before McGlashan runs forward to pick it up
full on middle and leg, driven straight to mid-on
misses out there, full toss on middle, flicked away to deep square leg, he could have hit that anywhere
sweetly timed, that raced off the bat, overpitched on the off stump, Yuvraj makes room and creams that just a little wide of Guptill at deep cover, it had disappeared over the ropes in a blink
bowled short outside leg and nipped back in, struck Yuvraj high on the pads as he tried to turn that away, they get a leg bye
this a run-fest., full on leg stump, Tendulkar bends down and paddles it over the fine-leg boundary, beautifully struck, Southee, it seems, will be taken off soon
will feel he missed out, made room and Southee fired it in full outside off, tried to steer it past point but failed to reach it
Ruder gets the same treatment, you can't feed the batsmen with length deliveries when they're in such a mood, full on middle and Yuvraj smashes it a mile over deep midwicket
almost had him there, a slower yorker that Yuvraj failed to pick, somehow managed to get his bat  down at the right time, got an inside edge behind square
full outside off, Tendulkar drags it wide of mid-on for a single
brilliant fielding by McCullum, driven powerfully wide of him at mid-on and he throws himself to his right to pull off a superb one-handed save
dreadful bowling, full toss on middle, Tendulkar paddles it away, helping it to the fine-leg boundary, you can't bowl like that with a short fine in place
carnage! Full on middle and he whips it away through square leg, India coasting along now
makes no difference to Yuvraj, another length ball and he dispatches it over long-on, these two have transformed the tempo of this match
good comeback, yorker bowled on middle at 126 kmph, dug out back to the bowler
good length a touch too wide outside off, Yuvraj tries to slog it over midwicket, mistimes it, a slower ball that, bowled at113 kmph
we have a broken bat folks, low full toss on leg stump and Yuvraj tries to drill that through mid-on, strikes the bottom of the bat, splitting the surface
the demolition continues, slower ball bowled short outside off, cut away fiercely behind point, a valiant attempt by the fielder in the deep but in vain
and again, full on middle and off, Yuvraj strikes it powerfully in the direction of long-off, Broom flings himself to his left to stop that but it's just struck way too hard
full on the off stump, driven through the line to long-off, the field is spread out now
good length on the off stump, bunts it away to deep cover
slower ball bowled short on the off stump, dabbed to point off the front foot
full outside off, swung away a touch, driven to deep cover
round the wicket to the left hander, good length on middle and leg, worked away to fine leg
short of a length outside off, guided off the back foot to third man
good length on the off stump, defended off the front foot to cover, watchfully played
short outside off, tries to cut it towards third man, misses
tries to paddle it over short fine, is struck on the pads outside the line, desperate cry from Oram but the umpire is unfazed
short of a good length on the off stump, pushed off the back foot to mid-off
back of a length on the off stump, punched to long-off
slower ball bowled full outside off, opens the face to play it to point
another six! Elliot bowls a slow legspinner to Yuvraj, it's a half-tracker and he pulls it away over deep square leg, just above the fielder, for a big one

he's gone now! Short of a good length outside off and came back in just a touch, Yuvraj tried to punch that towards mid-off, got a thin inside edge and McGlashan, who's standing up, snapped a sharp chance
beaten first ball, bowled quick on a good length outside off and moved away, Dhoni played inside the line to that one and the ball just evaded the outside edge
turned away in front of midwicket for a single
too wide, short and Tendulkar stretches full length to cut, misses
full on the pads, flicked away towards deep square leg
good length on middle, defended off the front foot to midwicket, end of a successful over for the hosts
tossed up on middle and leg, lands short, worked away to deep square
shortish on middle, pushed to midwicket, Dhoni calls for a single and then decides to send Tendulkar back from halfway down the pitch, no harm done though
flighted on middle and leg, defended back to the bowler with a lunge
short of a length outside off, went straight on, Dhoni pushed at if off the back foot, got a thick outside edge that beat point
tossed up on middle, pushed off the front foot to midwicket
missed stumping, pushed through quick outside off, comes down the track and then decides to work it away on the leg side, misses and McGlashan makes a mess of it behind the stumps
fuller ball on middle, driven off the front foot to mid-on
swats it wide of mid-off for a single

short of a length outside off, struck powerfully wide of deep cover where Guptill dives full length to his right, manages to drag it back in but then kicks it over the ropes just as he's trying to get back on his feet
pushed off the back foot to Guptill again

sweetly struck, he's into the 90's now, was not to the pitch there, bowled on a good length outside off, he made room and lofted it cleanly over the long-off boundary, went through with the shot, had made up his mind early
full on middle and off, turned away but straight to midwicket
short of a good length on middle, defended back to the bowler
pushed into the off side wide of cover
on middle and leg, worked away behind square for a single
tossed up outside off, reaches forward to defend
short outside off and spins into Dhoni, he makes room and punches it to deep cover
full on middle, mistimes a drive to midwicket
good length on middle, gets forward, closes the face and pushes it to mid-on
full outside off, driven firmly down the ground to long-off
short on the off stump, pushed off the back foot to long-off
that fielder's made busy again, struck down the ground straight to him for a single
and again, full outside off, driven with a full face for a single
short on middle, turned away off the back foot to deep midwicket
Dhoni joins the party, flighted outside off, lands full, in the slot, he charges down and pulverizes it over long-on
similar ball but drives it down the ground to long-on
good length on the off stump, pushed back to Patel
full on the off stump, pushed firmly to long-on
short of a length outside off and spins in, played off the back foot to cover
down the track and bunts it to long-off for a single
good length on middle and leg, dropped towards midwicket
short of a good length on leg stump, works it away behind square for a single
short of a length on the off stump, defended into the off side
full outside off, pushed firmly wide of mid-off, he gets a quick single, makes it easily even as the fielder aims accurately at the stumps at the non-striker's end
full outside off, drilled down the ground to mid-off
Hundred No. 43 in ODIs for the great man, short of a length on middle and leg, turns it away stylishly behind square to reach the landmark, an excellent innings, his first century in New Zealand
tossed up on middle and off, pushed towards deep square leg
struck fiercely to cover where a fumble allows them a single

he's cutting loose now, not there to the pitch, fired in quick on a good length on the off stump, he charges down and smashes it over long-off, played with a slightly open face there, still managed to clear the ropes
classy, low full toss outside off, he makes room and slices it away over point, delightful batting this
quicker ball bowled full outside leg stump, chased Tendulkar as he made room, struck on the pads and they get a leg bye
quicker ball fired in full on the off stump, dug out to the bowler
short of a length on middle, whipped away to deep midwicket
short outside off, swats it towards long-off
full on the off stump, paddled away straight to short fine, they manage a single
short of a good length outside off, slapped in front of square to deep cover
full on the leg stump and seemed to be sliding down, Tendulkar tried to flick it behind square, struck on the pads, big appeal turned down
full outside off, pushed off the front foot to deep cover and an overthrow allows them another single
short of a length outside off, pushed off the back foot to deep cover
back of a length outside off, guided off the back foot to third man
short of a length outside off, opens the face to push it to point
full on middle, chipped over midwicket for three runs, straight in the gap between deep midwicket and long-on
abysmal bowling from Mills, bowls a full toss on middle, Tendulkar gets across and paddles it over short fine for a one bounce four
full outside off, gets back and just bunts it to deep cover
full outside off stump, sliced towards deep point
full on the off stump, driven firmly down the ground to long-on
dropped, full outside off, makes room and tries to slice that over short-third where Elliot fails to hold on to a sharp chance jumping to his left
length ball on the off stump, driven to long-off
full toss outside off, steered through point into the deep for a couple
picked it up beautifully, full on middle, gets under it and strikes it cleanly over midwicket
good length outside off, pushed firmly to cover who misfields and allows the batsmen to take a single
full toss on the off stump, struck straight to cover, will feel he missed out there
just short of Ryder at long-off, full toss on middle, comes down the track and lofts it straight towards him, he slips as he tries to run forward to take that, nothing going right for the hosts
short of a length on the off stump, pushed off the back foot through the covers
fine leg has been pushed back, full outside leg stump, sweeps it straight to him
good length on middle, much better over, comes down the track and plays it to long-on for a single
smashed, full on middle, Dhoni makes room and drills that down the ground past the bowler, an ankle breaker that, Southie did a good job of evading it
slower ball bowled short outside off, slapped towards deep cover for a single
full outside off, slices it over point for a couple more
stellar shot, length ball again but they have to be dealt with, he's done it superbly here, makes room and just jabs it wide of cover, no effort there, just timing
full on middle and leg, glanced down to fine leg, brings up the 300
slapped back past the bowler, another length ball, hit straight to long-off
full toss on the off stump, driven to long-off for a single
atrocious bowling, full toss on leg stump and Tendulkar glances it down fine, a gift really, hands this pair a century partnership
full outside off, sliced away to deep point
another full toss but Dhoni misses out, pulls it away straight to deep midwicket
full on the off stump, chips it towards long-off, fell just short
full outside off, goes for the sweep this time, struck on the pads outside the line
fullish outside off stump, makes room but mistimes a drive towards point, gets a single
overpitched on the off stump, driven down to long-off
reaches another landmark here, but an outstanding shot, fullish on the off stump, makes room and lofts it cleanly over a widish long-off
smashed through the cover region, overpitched again and he caresses that between long-off and deep cover
full on middle, has a wild swing at it, gets an inside edge to fine leg, he's in a bit of pain here, did he pulled a stomach muscle?
Dhoni transports this around 30 rows into the stands over long-on, overpitched on middle and he just jabs it, went off the middle, some timing there
full outside off, tries to paddle it fine, is struck on the pads outside the line, gets a leg bye
yorker length on middle, dig out into the leg side
driven down the ground to long-off for a single
beamer and Ryder immediately apologises, Tendulkar still in some pain, how long can he carry on?

what a shot! Battling through pain and still manages to clear the boundary, overpitched outside off and that's dismissed over the deep-cover boundary, felt his ribs immediately after playing that, he's in some trouble here
worked away to deep square leg, full on middle and leg
driven straight to cover off the front foot
full on middle and off, struck down to long-on
the length-ball fest continues, overpitched on middle, Dhoni makes room and slaps it powerfully down the ground, long-on running to his left has no chance
yorker length on the off stump, dug out into the off side for a single
good length on the off stump, dragged down to midwicket
not there to hit but still manages to clear the boundary, bowled on a good length outside off and just heaves it over midwicket for a big one
goodness gracious, another one, full on middle, gets under it and dismisses it over the deep-midwicket boundary
short on middle, pulls it away to deep square leg
short of a good length outside off, chops it behind point for a single
back of a length on middle, turns it away off the back foot through midwicket for a well-run couple
short on middle, worked away off the back foot through the same region, but the fielder in the deep is quick on his feet and keeps them to a single
full outside off, driven off the front foot to deep cover
short of a good length on the off stump, pushed to mid-off, who's at the edge of the circle, for a single
short of a good length on the off stump, swatted down the ground for a single, the ball's a fly, and Dhoni's bat the the thing that you swat it with, no idea what it's called
overpitched again, on middle stump, Raina gets under it and smashes it straight over the bowler's head
brings up Southee's century, with the ball, full outside off, makes room and lofts it cleanly over extra cover
dropped into the leg side for a single, good length on middle and leg
short and wide, makes room and carts it wide of extra cover to beat long-off and deep cover
slower ball bowled full on the off stump, sliced away to extra cover, who's standing on the edge of the circle
the first bouncer of the day, where was it all this while, Millis bangs it in short on middle and Raina ducks, a few more of those earlier would have definitely helped
yorker length on the off stump, Raina digs it out back to Mills, two dot balls
full outside off, driven uppishly towards deep cover, gets a single
Dhoni goes after an excellent cameo, short on middle, tries to pull it away over deep square leg, gets the top edge and McGlashan runs back to take a well judged catch on the second attempt
full outside off, steered straight to point, an excellent over this
good length outside off, creamed to McCullum at cover who fields well diving to his left, Mills did a good job there
full outside off, steers it to third man for a single
full toss outside off, slapped to deep cover
dreadful stuff from Ryder, full toss outside off and Raina slashes it over deep point for one of the flattest sixes you'll ever see
full on middle, driven back to the bowler
full on middle again, another dot ball, mistimes a drive back to the bowler
decent comeback from Ryder after being hit for six, in the blockhole on the leg side, the most Raina can manage is a single towards midwicket

inn2.comm: good length outside off, tries to slash it away through point, misses
full outside off stump, tries to drive it to cover, gets an inside edge onto his pads
bowled on a length on middle and off, pushed back to the bowler
erring in length there, bowled short on middle, pulled away behind square, fine leg had no chance
yorker length on the off stump, dug out wide of mid-off for a quick single
full delivery on the off stump, driven on the front foot to mid-off
short outside off stump, bad start, pulled away in front of square towards deep midwicket for a couple
